==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|rights of first refusal}}

# {{lb|en|legal}} A [[provision]] in a [[contract]] that permits a [[party]] to that contract or another named party to have an [[opportunity]] to [[purchase]], [[use]], or otherwise [[obtain]] a specified object before it is offered to any other party.
